question.title: Maven - hangs on building a project

node.contents: Is it hanging with a busy CPU, or idle?

astNode.text: Is it hanging with a busy CPU, or idle?

node.contents: nope, it just sits there when it starts to compile

node.contents: No idea. You will need to dump some extra information. I don't think there is a limit for number of modules for a project.

astNode.text: No idea. You will need to dump some extra information. I don't think there is a limit for number of modules for a project.

node.contents: Does running with "mvn -X -e compile" reveal anything interesting? Perhaps post the logs somewhere.

astNode.text: Does running with "mvn -X -e compile" reveal anything interesting? Perhaps post the logs somewhere.

node.contents: Get the (maven/javacc) process PID and execute 'kill -3 PID' and see where it hangs, post the stack trace. Are you sure is in the compile phase? run maven with -X option to get more information...

astNode.text: Get the (maven/javacc) process PID and execute 'kill -3 PID' and see where it hangs, post the stack trace. Are you sure is in the compile phase? run maven with -X option to get more information...

node.contents: I am using maven to build projects that may or may not have children (not sure if that is related). I have many projects before this one that build fine, but this one just sits there. It doesn't have anything special in the pom.xml, but it just hangs during the compile phase.

node.contents: Any ideas what I can do? Is there a limit on the number of children a project can have?
